part:
Client-Side Framework




        Of the two sides of Vaadin, the client-side code runs as JavaScript in the
        web browser. You can create pure client-side applications and widgets in
        Java, which you compile to JavaScript that runs in the browser. You can
        integrate the client-side widgets with server-side components using
        connectors, and hence enable using them in pure server-side applications.



